3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed codes in terms of puncturing, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed codes in terms of puncturing, which is a topic related to social and information networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the design of LDPC codes, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures.
